      <p><span>We may use the information collected through certain functions for our other services. We could, for example, when you use a function or service of the information we collect, in another function or service to provide specific content to you or your friends, including but not limited to display ads (you can know more in about AD pages), have you read the content of information security of class, based on the characteristics of the labels suggest indirectly portraits and provides more precise and personalized services and content, etc.</span><br /><span>To secure our services and help us better understand how our application is performing, we may record relevant information, such as how often you use the application, crash data, overall usage, performance data, and where the application came from. We will not combine the information we store in our analytics software with any personally identifiable information you provide in your application.</span><br /><span>If we use your personal Information in a way that is not directly or reasonably relevant to the purpose for which it was collected, we will notify you again and obtain your express consent before using your personal Information.</span></p>
      <p><strong><span>5. Offer</span></strong></p>
      <p><span>At this time, we do not actively share or transfer your personal information to third parties outside Ops. In the event of any other sharing or transfer of your personal information to third parties outside Ops where you require us to share or transfer your personal information to third parties outside Ops, we will directly or confirm that third parties have obtained your express consent to do so.</span><br /><span>We will not publicly disclose the personal information we collect. If necessary, we will inform you of the purpose of this public disclosure, the type of information disclosed and the sensitive information that may be involved, and we will obtain your express consent.</span><br /><span>When you log in to an application run by a third-party entity via Ops personal account, we will provide your personal information to such third-party entity. The specific scope of external provision is subject to your confirmation in the interactive page. In addition, we will not provide your personal information to such third parties without your express consent.</span><br /><span>As our business continues to grow, we may enter into mergers, acquisitions, asset transfers and other transactions, and we will inform you of the circumstances, the continued protection of your personal information in accordance with laws and regulations and standards not lower than those required by this Guidance or the requirement that new controllers continue to protect your personal information.</span><br /><span>In addition, in accordance with relevant laws, regulations and national standards, we may share, transfer or publicly disclose personal information in the following situations without prior authorization and consent of the subject of personal information:</span></p>
